\section{Experimental Validation}

\subsection{Datasets and Fitting Procedure}

We test the transport integral model on three independent datasets:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Jarmola et al. (2012)} \cite{Jarmola2012}: $T_1(T)$ for three
    NV ensemble samples (S2, S8, S3) spanning 4--420\,K.
    \item \textbf{Lin et al. (2021)} \cite{Lin2021}: $T_1(T)$ for an NV ensemble
    sample spanning 300--600\,K.
    \item \textbf{Barbosa et al. (2024)} \cite{Barbosa2024}: $T_1(T)$ for NV
    centers in nanodiamond spanning 294--348\,K (included as qualitative
    evidence only).
\end{enumerate}

Parameter uncertainties were evaluated using bootstrap resampling
($10^4$ iterations). Because the Jarmola data were digitized from published
figures, the quoted uncertainties should be regarded as effective fit
uncertainties.

